###  1. Summary of the impact 

 Immunotherapy is now an established pillar of cancer treatment, improving the outcomes of patients with a wide variety of cancers. Professors James Larkin and Kevin Harrington at The Institute of Cancer Research \(ICR\) have facilitated the international approval and use of a range of immunotherapies through their roles as investigators in clinical trials, and by providing expert clinical opinion at regulatory committee review meetings. These immunotherapies include: 

-  **Ipilimumab in combination with nivolumab** for the treatment of advanced melanoma; 

-  **Avelumab in combination with axitinib** for the treatment of renal cancer; 

-  **Nivolumab** as a second\-line therapy in patients with recurrent or metastatic head and neck cancer; 

-  **Pembrolizumab** as a first\-line treatment in head and neck cancer; and 

-  **Talimogene laherparepvec** \(trade name T\-VEC\) for treating inoperable metastatic melanoma—the first approved oncolytic virus therapy.

